I What are the advantages of Bootstrap?
answer: Bootstrap is free to access for developers and open source for all.
1. Bootstrap provides a responsive layout, and template design.
2. We can customize changes in layout and templates.
3. Bootstrap adapts varius screen sizes from desktop to mobile.
4. It's time-saving.


II What is a Bootstrap Container, and how does it work?
answer: Bootstrap Container is a fixed layout. It Provides a responsive grid system for any devices and multiple screens.
It's the main block of any block of Bootstrap layout.
Example
<div class="container">
  <!-- Your content goes here -->
  <h1>Hello, Bootstrap!</h1>
  <p>This is a Bootstrap container.</p>
</div>


III What are the default Bootstrap text settings? There are Bootstrap default settings with examples..
Example
font-family: Sans-Serif;
font-weight: 400(normal text), 700(for headings);
font-size: 16px(1rem);
text-color: #000(black);
text-align: left;


IV What do you know about the Bootstrap Grid System?
The Bootstrap grid system is a responsive and flexible layouts for different types of screens.

1. 12-Grid columns: The grid system is based on a 12 columns layouts for different screen sizes.
2. Responsiveness: Bootstrap grid system is set responsively. It means automatically adjust and fit to content varius screen sizes from mobile to desktop.
3. Classes: We can use classes for CSS like (col-sm, col-md, col-lg. For small medium and large).
4. Customisation: We can use customize grid system as project needs.
Here is some examples..
Example
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">Column 1</div>
    <div class="col-md-4 offset-md-1">Column 2 with offset</div>
  </div>
</div>


V What is the difference between Bootstrap 4 and Bootstrap 5
Here are some differences between Bootstrap 4 and Bootstrap 5:
jQuery dependency
A; Bootstrap 4 had jQuery for some interactive components and functionalities, as drop-down and modals.
B; Bootstrap 5 removed the jQuery dependency, making it a lighter framework and improving performance.

Flexibility in all features:
A; Bootstrap 5 is more then flexible /bootstrap 4.
Example:
(1)classes, (2) components, (3)Layouts, etc..


VI What is a Button Group, and what is the class for a basic Button Group?
Button Group is a container who is all buttons.
As below an example..
Example
<div class="btn-group" role="group" aria-label="Basic example">
  <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Button 1</button>
  <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary">Button 2</button>
  <button type="button" class="btn btn-success">Button 3</button>
</div>
So that is a group of buttons.


VII How can you use Bootstrap to make thumbnails?
1.Create the main div as a container and give them a class ".thunmbnail".
2. Create a image tag and give the URL inside. So that is our thumbnail.
3. You can also include a <div> and give a class ".captain" and then add some additional content below the image.
4. Inside the "caption" div, you can add <h3> for thumbnail and for the discription or additional content give <p> tag inside the ".caption"  div.
Example
<div class="thumbnail">
  <img src="image.jpg" alt="Image">
  <div class="caption">
    <h3>Thumbnail Label</h3>
    <p>Description or additional content goes here.</p>
    </div>
</div>


VIII In Bootstrap 4, what is flexbox?
Flexbox is a CSS layout system used to create flexible and responsive web page layouts. Flexbox is designed to distribute space along a single axis (horizontally or vertically),
making it easier to align and distribute elements within a container.
Bootstrap 4 is a css layout system used to create flexible layout as total width or height.
Flexbox is distributing space horizontally or vertically and then fits into a container.
Example
 <div class="container d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center" >
        <div>
             <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
            <p>This is a simple example of a responsive layout using Bootstrap 4 flexbox classes.</p>
        </div>
    </div>


IX How can one create an alert in Bootstrap?
Ans: Create a div and give a class for alert. Then give a color like red ".alert alert-danger". And give a role ".alert".
Example
<div class="alert alert-primary" role="alert">
  This is a primary alert.
</div>


X What is a bootstrap card and how would you create one?
Ans: Bootstrap Cards is block to use display varius content like (links, images, texts, etc..);
Example:
<div class="card">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title">Card Title</h5>
    <p class="card-text">Some quick example text to build on the card.</p>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Go somewhere</a>
  </div>
</div>
